# FluCore — Convenciones SQL y RLS

## Nomenclatura SQL

| Elemento | Convención | Ejemplo |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| Tablas | `snake_case` plural | `ticket_logs`, `inventory_items` |
| Columnas | `snake_case` | `tenant_id`, `created_at` |
| Índices | `idx_{tabla}_{columna}` | `idx_tickets_tenant_status` |
| Triggers | `trg_{tabla}_{descripcion}` | `trg_tickets_updated_at` |
| Políticas | `"{tabla}_{operacion}"` | `"tickets_select"` |

## RLS — Patrón obligatorio (NUNCA usar FOR ALL)

```sql
-- ✅ CORRECTO — granular por operación
ALTER TABLE [tabla] ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

CREATE POLICY "[tabla]_select" ON [tabla]
  FOR SELECT USING (tenant_id = (auth.jwt() ->> 'tenant_id')::uuid);

CREATE POLICY "[tabla]_insert" ON [tabla]
  FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (tenant_id = (auth.jwt() ->> 'tenant_id')::uuid);

CREATE POLICY "[tabla]_update" ON [tabla]
  FOR UPDATE USING (tenant_id = (auth.jwt() ->> 'tenant_id')::uuid);

CREATE POLICY "[tabla]_no_delete" ON [tabla]
  FOR DELETE USING (false);

-- ❌ MAL — FOR ALL no protege INSERT sin WITH CHECK
CREATE POLICY "tenant_isolation" ON [tabla]
  FOR ALL USING (tenant_id = (auth.jwt() ->> 'tenant_id')::uuid);
```

## Tablas con bloqueo total desde el cliente

```sql
-- ticket_logs: auditoría inmutable — solo service role puede insertar
CREATE POLICY "ticket_logs_no_insert" ON ticket_logs FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (false);
CREATE POLICY "ticket_logs_no_update" ON ticket_logs FOR UPDATE USING (false);

-- tenants: solo el sistema crea/modifica tenants
CREATE POLICY "tenants_no_insert" ON tenants FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (false);

-- profiles: solo el backend Hono crea perfiles
CREATE POLICY "profiles_insert_block" ON profiles FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (false);
```

## Índices JSONB

```sql
-- ✅ jsonb_path_ops — más eficiente para @> y @?
CREATE INDEX idx_tickets_diag_gin ON tickets USING GIN (diagnostic_data jsonb_path_ops);

-- ❌ Sin operador — más grande, más lento
CREATE INDEX idx_tickets_diag_gin ON tickets USING GIN (diagnostic_data);
```

## Integridad cross-tenant — usar triggers, NO CHECK

```sql
-- ❌ MAL — PostgreSQL no admite subqueries en CHECK
ALTER TABLE tickets ADD CONSTRAINT fk_check
  CHECK (tenant_id = (SELECT tenant_id FROM equipment WHERE id = equipment_id));

-- ✅ CORRECTO — trigger BEFORE INSERT OR UPDATE
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION validate_ticket_equipment_tenant()
RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
BEGIN
  IF NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM equipment WHERE id = NEW.equipment_id AND tenant_id = NEW.tenant_id
  ) THEN
    RAISE EXCEPTION 'equipment % no pertenece al tenant %', NEW.equipment_id, NEW.tenant_id
      USING ERRCODE = 'foreign_key_violation';
  END IF;
  RETURN NEW;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql SECURITY DEFINER;
```

## Migrations — convención de nombres

```
001_core_schema.sql          → Schema base completo + RLS
002_jwt_hook.sql             → custom_access_token_hook
003_offline_sync_support.sql → Soporte offline-first
seed/001_medplan_seed.sql    → Datos iniciales (ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING)
```

## Storage RLS

```sql
CREATE POLICY "tenant_storage_isolation" ON storage.objects
  FOR ALL USING (
    bucket_id = 'flucore-vault'
    AND (storage.foldername(name))[1] = (auth.jwt() ->> 'tenant_id')
  );
```
